hands_on_practices.solution:
We are given $A=\begin{pmatrix}5&0\\0&50\end{pmatrix}$, $b=\begin{pmatrix}5\\50\end{pmatrix}$, $x_{k}=\begin{pmatrix}0.8\\0.9\end{pmatrix}$, and the Jacobi preconditioner $M=\operatorname{diag}(A)=\begin{pmatrix}5&0\\0&50\end{pmatrix}$. The original residual is $r_{k}=b-Ax_{k}$ and the preconditioned residual is $\hat{r}_{k}=M^{-1}(b-Ax_{k})$.

First compute the residual:
$$
r_{k}=b-Ax_{k}
=\begin{pmatrix}5\\50\end{pmatrix}-\begin{pmatrix}5&0\\0&50\end{pmatrix}\begin{pmatrix}0.8\\0.9\end{pmatrix}
=\begin{pmatrix}5-5\cdot 0.8\\50-50\cdot 0.9\end{pmatrix}
=\begin{pmatrix}1\\5\end{pmatrix}.
$$

Compute $M^{-1}$ and the preconditioned residual:
$$
M^{-1}=\begin{pmatrix}\frac{1}{5}&0\\0&\frac{1}{50}\end{pmatrix},
\quad
\hat{r}_{k}=M^{-1}r_{k}
=\begin{pmatrix}\frac{1}{5}&0\\0&\frac{1}{50}\end{pmatrix}\begin{pmatrix}1\\5\end{pmatrix}
=\begin{pmatrix}\frac{1}{5}\\\frac{1}{10}\end{pmatrix}.
$$

Compute the Euclidean norms:
$$
\|r_{k}\|_{2}=\sqrt{1^{2}+5^{2}}=\sqrt{26},\qquad
\|\hat{r}_{k}\|_{2}=\sqrt{\left(\frac{1}{5}\right)^{2}+\left(\frac{1}{10}\right)^{2}}
=\sqrt{\frac{1}{25}+\frac{1}{100}}
=\sqrt{\frac{5}{100}}
=\frac{\sqrt{5}}{10}.
$$

Form the ratio and simplify:
$$
\frac{\|r_{k}\|_{2}}{\|\hat{r}_{k}\|_{2}}
=\frac{\sqrt{26}}{\frac{\sqrt{5}}{10}}
=10\cdot\frac{\sqrt{26}}{\sqrt{5}}
=10\cdot\frac{\sqrt{130}}{5}
=2\sqrt{130}.
$$
